{"analytics_identifier":"D103","base_path":"/government/organisations/government-actuarys-department","content_id":"02e01dc9-a4c4-46d9-b496-a618c89afe62","description":"We provide actuarial solutions, including financial risk analysis, modelling and advice, to support the UK public sector. GAD is a non-ministerial department.","details":{"acronym":"GAD","alternative_format_contact_email":"enquiries@gad.gov.uk","body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>We provide actuarial solutions, including financial risk analysis, modelling and advice, to support the UK public sector.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Government Actuary's Department\">GAD</abbr> is a non-ministerial department.</p>\n</div>","brand":"hm-treasury","foi_exempt":false,"logo":{"crest":"single-identity","formatted_title":"Government <br/>Actuary&#39;s <br/>Department"},"ordered_corporate_information_pages":[{"href":"/government/organisations/government-actuarys-department/about/accessible-documents-policy","title":"Accessible documents policy"},{"href":"/government/organisations/government-actuarys-department/about/our-governance","title":"Our governance"},{"href":"/government/organisations/government-actuarys-department/about/terms-of-reference","title":"Terms of reference"},{"href":"/government/organisations/government-actuarys-department/about/recruitment","title":"Working for GAD"},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/government-actuarys-department/about/recruitment#vacancies-at-gad","title":"Jobs"}],"ordered_featured_documents":[{"document_type":"Blog post","href":"https://actuaries.blog.gov.uk/2026/05/12/from-data-gaps-to-decisions-qualitative-climate-scenario-analysis/","image":{"alt_text":"Three views depicting climate. Credit: iStock Photo","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6a043d6a4fb0713aa63ea840/s712_World_temperature___climate_change_-iStock.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6a043d6acd2e0e8b5b20b503/s465_World_temperature___climate_change_-iStock.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6a043d6acd2e0e8b5b20b504/World_temperature___climate_change_-iStock.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2026-05-13T00:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Mind the (data) gap. Qualitative climate scenario analysis can help public sector organisations understand risks and build resilience when the data needed for robust quantification is limited.</p>\n</div>","title":"From data gaps to decisions: Qualitative climate scenario analysis"},{"document_type":"Blog post","href":"https://actuaries.blog.gov.uk/2026/05/05/why-are-women-living-over-a-quarter-of-their-lives-in-poor-health/","image":{"alt_text":"Older woman sits checks her blood pressure using machine. Credit: iStock Photo","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69fa14f9845a5bf0c2641dcd/s712_Older_woman_checks_blood_pressure_-_iStock.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69fa14f9c2aae644ed2aba11/s465_Older_woman_checks_blood_pressure_-_iStock.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69fa14f99959f6be3b453583/Older_woman_checks_blood_pressure_-_iStock.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2026-05-05T00:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>While healthy life expectancy in the UK continues to decrease, the gap between HLE and life expectancy has widened, especially for women. Actuary Natasha Hill explores why women may be living such a large proportion of their lives in poor health.</p>\n</div>","title":"Why are women living over a quarter of their lives in poor health?"},{"document_type":"News story","href":"/government/news/climate-scenario-analysis","image":{"alt_text":"Royal Courts of Justice. Credit: Unsplash","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69f36aafab602a88957eef6e/s712_Royal_Courts_of_Justice_.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69f36aaf4b0f7395324fbb91/s465_Royal_Courts_of_Justice_.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69f36aaf4b0f7395324fbb93/Royal_Courts_of_Justice_.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2026-04-30T15:35:18.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>GAD helped the Ministry of Justice understand how climate change could affect its services, finances and estate, supporting better long-term planning.</p>\n</div>","title":"Climate scenario analysis"},{"document_type":"Blog post","href":"https://actuaries.blog.gov.uk/2026/04/29/the-year-ahead-public-service-pension-administration-2026-2027/","image":{"alt_text":"Woman with Clipboard and Laptop","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69f365905c1bc131b7d1ebb5/s712_Woman_with_Clipboard_and_Laptop_960x640.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69f365905c1bc131b7d1ebb6/s465_Woman_with_Clipboard_and_Laptop_960x640.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69f36590161a319cff4fbb95/Woman_with_Clipboard_and_Laptop_960x640.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2026-04-29T00:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>As we move into the 2026 to 2027 financial year, pension scheme administration continues to face unprecedented challenges.</p>\n</div>","title":"The year ahead: public service pension administration - 2026-2027"},{"document_type":"Blog post","href":"https://actuaries.blog.gov.uk/2026/04/10/developing-climate-related-health-insights/","image":{"alt_text":"People in London street near a bus stop. Credit: Unsplash.","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69d9278d96c86b7513170244/s712_People_in_London_-_Lawrence_Krowdeed__Unsplash.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69d9278deb7e7bc56517024d/s465_People_in_London_-_Lawrence_Krowdeed__Unsplash.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69d9278dd3e08b8871b665c6/People_in_London_-_Lawrence_Krowdeed__Unsplash.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2026-04-10T00:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>GAD’s new climate and health group brings together expert analysis to help public sector clients understand climate-related health risks in long-term planning.</p>\n</div>","title":"Developing climate-related health insights"},{"document_type":"Blog post","href":"https://actuaries.blog.gov.uk/2026/03/30/not-all-years-lived-are-equal-understanding-measures-of-health/","image":{"alt_text":"People exercising in an outdoor fitness class. Credit: Gabin Vallet, Unsplash","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69ca92fa95a323ea3496ed5d/s712_Outdoor_fitness_class_-_Gabin_Vallet__Unsplash.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69ca92fab111d64c49bb3d87/s465_Outdoor_fitness_class_-_Gabin_Vallet__Unsplash.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69ca92fa95a323ea3496ed5c/Outdoor_fitness_class_-_Gabin_Vallet__Unsplash.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2026-03-30T00:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>HLE and QALYs both measure health quality and quantity - but they’re built differently, used differently, and answer different policy questions. Find out more in this blog from Natasha Hill.</p>\n</div>","title":"Not all years lived are equal: understanding measures of health"}],"ordered_featured_links":[{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gad-services/government-actuarys-department-services","title":"GAD services"},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/staff-transfers","title":"Staff transfers (Fair Deal)"},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gad-publications/gad-publications","title":"Publications and events"},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/gad-case-studies","title":"Case studies"},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/government-actuarys-department/about/recruitment","title":"Working for GAD"}],"ordered_promotional_featu